          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-6">4. Third-Party Cookies</h2>
          <div class="text-gray-300 space-y-6">

            <p>We use carefully selected third-party services that may set their own cookies. All third-party cookies require your consent.</p>

            <div class="space-y-4">

              <div class="bg-gray-900/50 p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-800">
                <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
                  <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-white">Google Analytics</h3>
                  <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-cyan-400 hover:text-cyan-300 text-sm">Privacy Policy ↗</a>
                </div>
                <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-200 mb-2">Purpose:</h4>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Website analytics and usage insights</p>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-200 mb-2">Privacy Settings:</h4>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">IP anonymization enabled, no ads features</p>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-200 mb-2">Opt-out:</h4>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Available through cookie preferences</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-gray-900/50 p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-800">
                <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
                  <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-white">Sentry</h3>
                  <a href="https://sentry.io/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-cyan-400 hover:text-cyan-300 text-sm">Privacy Policy ↗</a>
                </div>
                <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-200 mb-2">Purpose:</h4>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Error monitoring and performance tracking</p>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-200 mb-2">Privacy Settings:</h4>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">PII filtering enabled, no user tracking</p>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-200 mb-2">Data Collected:</h4>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Technical errors and performance metrics only</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

            </div>

            <div class="bg-orange-900/30 border border-orange-700 p-4 rounded-lg">
              <h4 class="text-orange-200 font-medium mb-2">Third-Party Control</h4>
              <p class="text-orange-200 text-sm">
                While we carefully select and configure third-party services for privacy, each service operates under its own privacy policy.
                We recommend reviewing the privacy policies of any third-party services you consent to.
              </p>
            </div>

          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Cookie Management -->
        <section id="cookie-management" class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-6">5. Managing Your Cookie Preferences</h2>
          <div class="text-gray-300 space-y-6">

            <p>You have full control over which cookies we can use on your device. You can manage your preferences in several ways:</p>

            <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">

              <div class="bg-cyan-900/30 border border-cyan-700 p-6 rounded-lg">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-white mb-4">Our Cookie Preference Center</h3>
                <p class="text-cyan-200 mb-4 text-sm">
                  The easiest way to manage your cookie preferences is through our built-in preference center.
                </p>
                <button
                  id="open-cookie-preferences-main"
                  class="bg-cyan-600 hover:bg-cyan-700 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-lg text-sm font-medium transition-colors"
                >
                  Open Cookie Preferences
                </button>
                <div class="mt-4 text-cyan-200 text-sm">
                  <h4 class="font-medium mb-2">Features:</h4>
                  <ul class="space-y-1">
                    <li>• Granular control by category</li>
                    <li>• See what each cookie does</li>
                    <li>• Change preferences anytime</li>
                    <li>• Immediate effect</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-purple-900/30 border border-purple-700 p-6 rounded-lg">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-white mb-4">Browser Settings</h3>
                <p class="text-purple-200 mb-4 text-sm">
                  You can also control cookies through your browser's privacy settings.
                </p>
                <div class="text-purple-200 text-sm">
                  <h4 class="font-medium mb-2">Browser Options:</h4>
                  <ul class="space-y-1">
                    <li>• Block all cookies</li>
                    <li>• Block third-party cookies only</li>
                    <li>• Clear existing cookies</li>
                    <li>• Set cookie expiration rules</li>
                  </ul>
                  <p class="mt-3 text-xs text-purple-300">
                    <strong>Note:</strong> Blocking essential cookies may affect website functionality.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>

            </div>

            <div class="bg-green-900/30 border border-green-700 p-4 rounded-lg">
              <h4 class="text-green-200 font-medium mb-2">Do Not Track</h4>
              <p class="text-green-200 text-sm">
                We respect the "Do Not Track" browser header. If you have DNT enabled, we will only use essential cookies
                necessary for website functionality and will not track your browsing behavior.
              </p>
            </div>

          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Browser Settings -->
        <section id="browser-settings" class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-6">6. Browser Cookie Settings</h2>
          <div class="text-gray-300 space-y-6">

            <p>Here's how to manage cookies in popular browsers:</p>

            <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">

              <div class="bg-gray-900/50 p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800">
                <h3 class="font-medium text-white mb-3">Google Chrome</h3>
                <ol class="text-sm space-y-1 list-decimal list-inside">
                  <li>Click the three dots menu → Settings</li>
                  <li>Go to Privacy and security → Cookies and other site data</li>
                  <li>Choose your preferred cookie settings</li>
                  <li>Click "See all cookies and site data" to manage specific sites</li>
                </ol>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-gray-900/50 p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800">
                <h3 class="font-medium text-white mb-3">Mozilla Firefox</h3>
                <ol class="text-sm space-y-1 list-decimal list-inside">
                  <li>Click the menu button → Settings</li>
                  <li>Go to Privacy & Security</li>
                  <li>Under Cookies and Site Data, click "Manage Data"</li>
                  <li>Choose your cookie blocking preferences</li>
                </ol>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-gray-900/50 p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800">
                <h3 class="font-medium text-white mb-3">Safari</h3>
                <ol class="text-sm space-y-1 list-decimal list-inside">
                  <li>Go to Safari → Preferences</li>
                  <li>Click the Privacy tab</li>
                  <li>Choose your cookie and tracking settings</li>
                  <li>Click "Manage Website Data" for specific sites</li>
                </ol>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-gray-900/50 p-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-800">
                <h3 class="font-medium text-white mb-3">Microsoft Edge</h3>
                <ol class="text-sm space-y-1 list-decimal list-inside">
                  <li>Click the three dots menu → Settings</li>
                  <li>Go to Cookies and site permissions</li>
                  <li>Click "Cookies and data stored"</li>
                  <li>Manage your cookie preferences</li>
                </ol>
              </div>

            </div>

            <div class="bg-blue-900/30 border border-blue-700 p-4 rounded-lg">
              <h4 class="text-blue-200 font-medium mb-2">Mobile Browsers</h4>
              <p class="text-blue-200 text-sm mb-2">
                Cookie settings on mobile browsers are typically found in:
